p(x)=fx^2+gx+h
f+g+h=4
4f+2g+h=6
 16f+4g+h=1.
\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 1 & 1\\ 4 & 2 & 1\\ 16 & 4 & 1\end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix}f\\ g\\ h\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}4\\ 6\\ 1\end{pmatrix}.
 p(x) = \begin{pmatrix}x^2 & x & 1\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}f\\g\\h\end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix}x^2 & x & 1\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 1 & 1\\ 4 & 2 & 1\\ 16 & 4 & 1\end{pmatrix}^{-1}\begin{pmatrix}4\\ 6\\ 1\end{pmatrix}
=\begin{pmatrix}x^2 & x & 1\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix} 1/3 & -1/2 & 1/6\\ -2 & 5/2 & -1/2\\ 8/3 & -2 & 1/3\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}4\\ 6\\ 1\end{pmatrix}= \begin{pmatrix}x^2 & x & 1\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}-3/2\\13/2\\-1\end{pmatrix}
 = -\frac{3}{2}x^2+\frac{13}{2}x-1.
